    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Karlson Pfannschmidt</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:232px;\"><a href=\"https://github.com/kiudee\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/a/ac/KarlsonPfannschmidt.jpg\" width=\"230\" height=\"230\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:KarlsonPfannschmidt.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Karlson Pfannschmidt  <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Karlson Pfannschmidt</b>, (Kiudee)<br />\na German computer scientist specialized in <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">machine learning</a>, affiliated with the <a href=\"/Paderborn_University\" title=\"Paderborn University\">Paderborn University</a>.\nHe designed and published tools for local and distributed <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">tuning</a> of chess engines using state-of-the-art <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayesian_optimization\">Bayesian optimization</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.\nHis Bayesian implementation of a sequential model-based optimization, dubbed <b>Bayes-skopt</b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> was successfully applied to tune hyperparameters of <a href=\"/Leela_Chess_Zero\" title=\"Leela Chess Zero\">Leela Chess Zero</a> and its relatives <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selcted_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selcted Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selcted_Publications\">Selcted Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Karlson_Pfannschmidt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selcted Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eyke_H%C3%BCllermeier\">Eyke Hüllermeier</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://geb.uni-giessen.de/geb/volltexte/2014/10912/\">Susanne Held</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://hunderunden.de/hunderunden-mit/reto-neiger\">Reto Neiger</a> (<b>2016</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-319-40596-4_38\">Evaluating Tests in Medical Diagnosis: Combining Machine Learning with Game-Theoretical Concepts</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://is.ieis.tue.nl/ipmu/\">IPMU 2016</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.uni-paderborn.de/person/54803/\">Pritha Gupta</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eyke_H%C3%BCllermeier\">Eyke Hüllermeier</a> (<b>2018</b>). <i>Deep Architectures for Learning Context-dependent Ranking Functions</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.05796\">arXiv:1803.05796</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Karlson_Pfannschmidt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/lczero/ngXug9YPgGY/nEq-e9EIEAAJ\">Kiudee parameters are very strong</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Stefan_Pohl&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Stefan Pohl (page does not exist)\">Stefan Pohl</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">LCZero Forum</a>, January 20, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=72854\">Lc0: Kiudee setting is very strong</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Stefan_Pohl&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Stefan Pohl (page does not exist)\">Stefan Pohl</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 20, 2020</li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=72854&amp;start=23\">Re: Lc0: Kiudee setting is very strong</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 22, 2020</dd>\n<dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=72854&amp;start=33\">Re: Lc0: Kiudee setting is very strong</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 28, 2020</dd>\n<dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=72854&amp;start=36\">Re: Lc0: Kiudee setting is very strong</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 28, 2020</dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=72953\">Crazy good LTC Kiudee \"mod\" setting just by adjusting CPuct</a> by <a href=\"/Kai_Laskos\" title=\"Kai Laskos\">Kai Laskos</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 31, 2020</li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=72953&amp;start=10\">Re: Crazy good LTC Kiudee \"mod\" setting just by adjusting CPuct</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 31, 2020</dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=73684&amp;start=1\">Re: Lc0 soon to support chess960&#160;?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 18, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=73761\">Does Ordo incorporate priors correctly?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 25, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=73927\">New lc0 tune with kiudee tuner</a> by jjoshua2, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 14, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=74877&amp;start=11\">Re: Evaluation &amp; Tuning in Chess Engines</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Karlson Pfannschmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 25, 2020</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Karlson_Pfannschmidt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.uni-paderborn.de/person/13472/\">Karlson Pfannschmidt - Kontakt (Universität Paderborn)</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://chess-tuning-tools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\">Chess Tuning Tools</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/kiudee\">kiudee (Karlson Pfannschmidt) · GitHub</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/kiudee/chess-tuning-tools\">GitHub - kiudee/chess-tuning-tools</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/kiudee/bayes-skopt\">GitHub - kiudee/bayes-skopt: A fully Bayesian implementation of sequential model-based optimization</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.chessbase.com/post/fat-fritz-update-and-fat-fritz-jr\">Fat Fritz 1.1 update and a small gift</a> by <a href=\"/Albert_Silver\" title=\"Albert Silver\">Albert Silver</a>, <a href=\"/ChessBase\" title=\"ChessBase\">ChessBase News</a>, March 05, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Fat_Fritz\" title=\"Fat Fritz\">Fat Fritz</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Karlson_Pfannschmidt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/kiudee\">kiudee (Karlson Pfannschmidt) · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/kiudee/chess-tuning-tools\">GitHub - kiudee/chess-tuning-tools: A collection of scripts aimed at efficiently tuning chess engine parameters</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/kiudee/bayes-skopt\">GitHub - kiudee/bayes-skopt: A fully Bayesian implementation of sequential model-based optimization</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.chessbase.com/post/fat-fritz-update-and-fat-fritz-jr\">Fat Fritz 1.1 update and a small gift</a> by <a href=\"/Albert_Silver\" title=\"Albert Silver\">Albert Silver</a>, <a href=\"/ChessBase\" title=\"ChessBase\">ChessBase News</a>, March 05, 2020</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.uni-paderborn.de/person/13472/\">Karlson Pfannschmidt - Kontakt (Universität Paderborn)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Feline_